\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. octopodes} Turrill,{\i  Gard. Chron.} ser. 3, {\b 102}: 303 (1937). Stolons usually long, slender. Rosettes 2-2·5 cm in diameter. Leaves 7 × 3 mm, more or less erect, oblanceolate to obovate pubescent, with cilia becoming longer towards the reddish-brown apex. Flowering stem up to 9 cm, slender. Flowers few, 9-merous (rarely 10-merous); sepals purplish; petals 8 × 1·5 mm, pale yellow, tinged with lilac at the base; filaments purple. 2n = 34. •{\i  S.W. Makedonija} ({\i Baba Planina}). Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b S. thompsonianum} Wale, {\i Quart. Bull. Alp. Gard. Soc.}{\b  8}: 210 (1940), is probably a hybrid between {\b 4} and {\b 14}.
\par

